#. Tag: title
#: faq.docbook:8
#, no-c-format
msgid "Frequently Asked Questions (&FAQ;)"
msgstr "Pogosto zastavljena vprašanja (&FAQ;)"

#. Tag: primary
#: faq.docbook:10
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>FAQ</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>FAQ</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:12
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have problems with &krusader; please check the <ulink url=\"https://"
"krusader.org/get-involved/index.html\">installation procedure</ulink>, as "
"your problem may be caused by a bad installation."
msgstr ""
"Če imate težave z &krusader; preverite <ulink url=\"https://krusader.org/get-"
"involved/index.html\">postopek namestitve</ulink>, saj je vzrok vaše težave "
"lahko slaba namestitev."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:17
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &FAQ; is divided into three sections: <itemizedlist> <listitem> <para> "
"<link linkend=\"faq_installation\">Installation &FAQ;</link> (this page)</"
"para> </listitem> <listitem> <para> <link linkend=\"faq_usage\">Usage &FAQ;</"
"link> (issues with running/using &krusader;)</para> </listitem> <listitem> "
"<para> <link linkend=\"faq_general\">General &FAQ;</link> (bug reports, "
"forum, mailing list, ...)</para> </listitem> </itemizedlist>If you feel that "
"a &FAQ; is missing or if something is not clear to you, please <link linkend="
"\"editors_note\">let us know</link>."
msgstr ""
"&FAQ; je razdeljen na tri razdelke: <itemizedlist> <listitem> <para> <link "
"linkend=\"faq_installation\">Namestitev &FAQ;</link> (ta stran)</para> </"
"listitem> <listitem> <para> <link linkend=\"faq_usage\">Uporaba &FAQ;</link> "
"(težave pri izvajanju/uporabi &krusader;)</para> </listitem> <listitem> "
"<para> <link linkend=\"faq_general\">Splošno &FAQ;</link > (poročila o "
"napakah, forum, poštni seznam, ...)</para> </listitem> </itemizedlist>Če "
"menite, da &FAQ; manjka ali če vam kaj ni jasno, <link linkend=\"editors_note"
"\">nam sporočite</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: faq.docbook:40
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installation &FAQ;"
msgstr "Namestitev &FAQ;"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:44
#, no-c-format
msgid "Does &krusader; need &plasma; to run?"
msgstr "Ali &krusader; potrebujejo &plasma; teči?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:48
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>No, &krusader; does not need the &plasma; window manager</"
"emphasis> to run on your computer but &krusader;'s natural environment is "
"&plasma;, because it relies on services provided by the &kf5-full; base "
"libraries. Only some shared libraries are needed &eg; &kde-frameworks; "
"libraries, &Qt; libraries, &etc; This means that &krusader; runs on <ulink "
"url=\"https://www.gnome.org\"><application>GNOME</application></ulink>, "
"<ulink url=\"http://www.afterstep.org/\"><application>AfterStep</"
"application></ulink>, <ulink url=\"https://www.xfce.org/"
"\"><application>XFce</application></ulink> and other window managers "
"provided the appropriate libraries are installed on your computer. All this "
"is not a problem since the apt-get world can resolve these dependencies "
"instantly."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Ne, &krusader; ne potrebuje &plasma; upravitelja oken</emphasis> "
"za zagon na vašem računalniku, vendar je &krusader;ovo naravno okolje "
"&plasma;, ker se zanaša na storitve, ki jih ponuja &kf5-full; osnovne "
"knjižnice. Potrebne so le nekatere deljene knjižnice &eg; &kde-frameworks; "
"knjižnice, &Qt; knjižnice, &etc; To pomeni, da &krusader; deluje na <ulink "
"url=\"https://www.gnome.org\"><application>GNOME</application></ulink>, "
"<ulink url=\"http://www.afterstep.org/\"><application >AfterStep</"
"application></ulink>, <ulink url=\"https://www.xfce.org/"
"\"><application>XFce</application></ulink> in drugi upravitelji oken, če so "
"nameščene ustrezne knjižnice na vašem računalniku. Vse to ni problem, saj "
"lahko svet apt-get te odvisnosti razreši takoj."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:65
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You do not need to switch to the &plasma; window manager to use &krusader;; "
"you can still use <ulink url=\"https://www.gnome.org\"><application>GNOME</"
"application></ulink>, <ulink url=\"http://www.afterstep.org/"
"\"><application>AfterStep</application></ulink>, <ulink url=\"https://www."
"xfce.org/\"><application>XFce</application></ulink> or another window "
"manager. However, the configuration of the &krusader; fonts and some "
"behavior is done by running <command>systemsettings</command>."
msgstr ""
"Ni vam treba preklopiti na &plasma; upravitelj oken za uporabo &krusader;; "
"še vedno lahko uporabljate <ulink url=\"https://www.gnome.org"
"\"><application>GNOME</application></ulink>, <ulink url=\"http://www."
"afterstep.org/\"> <application>AfterStep</application></ulink>, <ulink url="
"\"https://www.xfce.org/\"><application>XFce</application></ulink> ali drug "
"upravitelj oken. Vendar pa konfiguracija programa &krusader; pisave in nekaj "
"vedenja izvedete z zagonom <command>systemsettings</command>."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:75
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A lot depends on what you want to do with &krusader;. You should know that "
"&krusader; uses the &kde-frameworks; KIO Slaves to access remote file "
"systems, and support for only a limited number of file system types are "
"shipped with &kde-frameworks; libraries, most of the KIO Slave are bundled "
"with &kf5-full; (including fish, sftp and tar)."
msgstr ""
"Veliko je odvisno od tega, kaj želite početi z &krusader;. Vedeti morate, da "
"&krusader; uporablja &kde-frameworks; KIO Slaves za dostop do oddaljenih "
"datotečnih sistemov in podpora le za omejeno število tipov datotečnih "
"sistemov so priloženi &kde-frameworks; knjižnicah je večina KIO Slave "
"priložena &kf5-full; (vključno z ribami, sftp in tar)."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:85
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To summarize, if you want a working &krusader; - install &kf5-full;. If you "
"want a functional &krusader; then you need &kf5-full; and some additional "
"&plasma; packages. For maximum functionality, &krusader; needs some &kde; "
"Applications (&ark;, &kdiff3;, <application>KRename</application>), but the "
"&plasma; window manager is optional."
msgstr ""
"Če povzamem, če želite delujoč &krusader; - namestite &kf5-full;. Če želite "
"funkcionalen &krusader; potem potrebujete &kf5-full; in nekaj dodatnih "
"&plasma; paketi. Za maksimalno funkcionalnost &krusader; potrebuje nekaj "
"&kde; Aplikacije (&ark;, &kdiff3;, <application>KRename</application>), "
"vendar &plasma; upravitelj oken ni obvezen."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:98
#, no-c-format
msgid "I cannot find a package for &krusader;, what to do?"
msgstr "Ne najdem paketa za &krusader;, kaj naj storim?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:102
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Check if your distribution provides &krusader;, if it does not then contact "
"your distribution creator and ask them to include &krusader;!"
msgstr ""
"Preverite, ali vaša distribucija ponuja &krusader;, če ne, se obrnite na "
"ustvarjalca distribucije in ga prosite, da vključi &krusader;!"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:106
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Did you take a look at the <ulink url=\"https://krusader.org/get-involved/"
"index.html\">installation procedure</ulink> page? If you have and found "
"nothing, you can always compile &krusader; from source. Feel free to post a "
"<link linkend=\"faqi_help_request\">help request</link> if you encounter "
"problems."
msgstr ""
"Ali ste si ogledali stran s <ulink url=\"https://krusader.org/get-involved/"
"index.html\">postopkom namestitve</ulink>? Če niste našli ničesar, lahko "
"vedno prevedete &krusader; iz vira. Če naletite na težave, lahko objavite "
"<link linkend=\"faqi_help_request\">prošnjo za pomoč</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:120
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"I am having trouble compiling and installing &krusader;, how do I send a "
"help request?"
msgstr ""
"Imam težave pri prevajanju in namestitvi &krusader;, kako naj pošljem "
"zahtevo za pomoč?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:125
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Please read our detailed <ulink url=\"https://krusader.org/get-involved/"
"index.html\">installation procedure</ulink> and the <link linkend=\"faq"
"\">FAQ</link>. If you cannot find a solution to your problem then feel free "
"to post a <emphasis role=\"bold\">help request</emphasis> at our &krusader; "
"forum or use the <ulink url=\"https://groups.google.com/group/krusader-users"
"\">&krusader;-users</ulink> mailing list. But before posting a help request, "
"please try the following:"
msgstr ""
"Preberite naš podroben <ulink url=\"https://krusader.org/get-involved/index."
"html\">namestitveni postopek</ulink> in <link linkend=\"faq\">pogosta "
"vprašanja</link>. Če ne najdete rešitve za svojo težavo, objavite <emphasis "
"role=\"bold\">prošnjo za pomoč</emphasis> na našem &krusader; forum ali "
"uporabite poštni seznam <ulink url=\"https://groups.google.com/group/"
"krusader-users\">&krusader;-users</ulink>. Toda preden objavite zahtevo za "
"pomoč, poskusite naslednje:"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:136
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the search function on the <ulink url=\"https://forum.kde.org/viewforum."
"php?f=225\">&kde; Forum</ulink>, your problem might be solved or discussed "
"already."
msgstr ""
"Uporabite funkcijo iskanja na <ulink url=\"https://forum.kde.org/viewforum."
"php?f=225\">&kde; Forum</ulink>, vaš problem je morda rešen ali o njem že "
"razpravljamo."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you cannot find a solution, please make a note of the following issues: "
"<itemizedlist> <listitem> <para>the &krusader; version used</para> </"
"listitem> <listitem> <para>the &Linux; distribution + version used</para> </"
"listitem> <listitem> <para>a good description of the problem</para> </"
"listitem> </itemizedlist>Without this information, it is very difficult for "
"us to help you."
msgstr ""
"Če ne najdete rešitve, si zapišite naslednje težave: <itemizedlist> "
"<listitem> <para>seznam &krusader; uporabljena različica</para> </listitem> "
"<listitem> <para>&Linux; distribucija + uporabljena različica</para> </"
"listitem> <listitem> <para>dober opis težave</para> </listitem> </"
"itemizedlist>Brez teh informacij vam bomo zelo težko pomagali."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:157
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you give us the error messages (&eg; <command>make</command> error "
"messages) please start with the FIRST error message, all the error messages "
"which follow the first error message are consequences and not the cause of "
"your problem."
msgstr ""
"Če nam pošljete sporočila o napakah (&eg; sporočila o napakah <command>make</"
"command>), začnite s PRVIM sporočilom o napaki, vsa sporočila o napaki, ki "
"sledijo prvemu sporočilu o napaki, so posledice in ne vzrok vaše težave."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:167
#, no-c-format
msgid "Send out your help request."
msgstr "Pošljite svojo prošnjo za pomoč."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:170 faq.docbook:701 faq.docbook:904
#, no-c-format
msgid "Thank you for your co-operation!"
msgstr "Hvala za sodelovanje!"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:177
#, no-c-format
msgid "Why does &krusader;-git show an old version number in the about box?"
msgstr "Zakaj &krusader;-git prikaže številko stare različice v oknu o?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:181
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Because we only change the version number just before we do a new release. "
"&krusader;-git will show an older version number, so ignore the version "
"number and check the download date. We simply have not yet decided what the "
"next version number will be."
msgstr ""
"Ker številko različice spremenimo samo tik preden naredimo novo izdajo. "
"&krusader;-git bo prikazal starejšo številko različice, zato prezrite "
"številko različice in preverite datum prenosa. Preprosto se še nismo "
"odločili, katera bo naslednja številka različice."

#. Tag: title
#: faq.docbook:193
#, no-c-format
msgid "Usage &FAQ;"
msgstr "Uporaba &FAQ;"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:197
#, no-c-format
msgid "Why does &krusader; freeze or hang on a dead mountpoint?"
msgstr "Zakaj &krusader; zamrzne ali visi na mrtvi točki priklopa?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:201
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When &krusader; is &eg; browsing an &NFS; share and the &NFS; server goes "
"down, &krusader; will freeze. This &krusader; (and all other open internal "
"viewers/editors) freeze is fatal, and can only be corrected with the "
"<command>kill -9</command>. We have no solution for this. This is an issue "
"not confined to file managers, or even the &Linux; OS! The problem is that "
"you <quote>hang</quote> on the first access to the dead share - so there is "
"no way around it, no check to avoid it, even <command>ls</command> will "
"freeze. Just trying to read something - anything - is enough to get you "
"stuck. The one and only way around this architectural problem is using a "
"multi-threaded design - this way if we get stuck, we do not hang the entire "
"application event loop, but we do not think that the time is right for "
"adding threads, we are not sure that *all* the &kde-frameworks; systems out "
"there are using &Qt;-mt (the multi threaded version of the &Qt; library), "
"and the &krusader; Krew may not be the right people to address this major "
"issue in any case; so currently this is just a bug we have to learn to live "
"with."
msgstr ""
"Ko &krusader; je &eg; brskanje po &NFS; skupno rabo in &NFS; strežnik ne "
"deluje, &krusader; bo zmrznilo. Ta &krusader; (in vsi drugi odprti notranji "
"pregledovalniki/urejevalniki) je zamrznitev usodna in jo lahko popravite le "
"z ukazom <command>kill -9</command>. Za to nimamo rešitve. To je težava, ki "
"ni omejena na upravitelje datotek ali celo &Linux; OS! Težava je v tem, da "
"<quote>visite</quote> pri prvem dostopu do mrtvega deleža - tako da ni "
"nobene možnosti zaobiti tega, ni preverjanja, da bi se temu izognili, celo "
"<command>ls</command> bo zamrznil. Dovolj je, da nekaj preberete – karkoli "
"–, da se zataknete. Edina in edina rešitev tega arhitekturnega problema je "
"uporaba večnitne zasnove - na ta način, če se nam zatakne, ne prekinemo "
"celotne zanke dogodkov aplikacije, vendar menimo, da ni pravi čas za "
"dodajanje niti, nisem prepričan, da *vsa* ogrodja &kde-frameworks; sistemi "
"uporabljajo &Qt;-mt (večnitna različica knjižnice &Qt;) in &krusader; moštvo "
"v vsakem primeru morda ni pravi ljudje za reševanje tega velikega vprašanja; "
"tako da je trenutno to le hrošč, s katerim se moramo naučiti živeti."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:230
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When I try to resize &krusader; to make it smaller, I discover that I cannot "
"resize it below a certain size. Why?"
msgstr ""
"Ko poskušam spremeniti velikost &krusader; da ga pomanjšam, ugotovim, da ga "
"ne morem spremeniti pod določeno velikost. Zakaj?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:235
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See the <guibutton>F1, F2</guibutton> (&etc;) buttons? They are not allowing "
"&krusader; to downsize as they have a minimum size. Just disable them "
"<menuchoice> <guimenu>Settings</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Show FN Keys Bar</"
"guimenuitem> </menuchoice> and you will be able to resize &krusader; to your "
"liking. Since version 1.51 we have improved this greatly: when downsizing "
"the buttons will look like 'F5 ..py'. When the button faces are too small to "
"read a tooltip will give the complete text. The minimum width is 45 pixels "
"for each button."
msgstr ""
"Vidite gumbe <guibutton>F1, F2</guibutton> (&etc;)? Ne dovolijo &krusader; "
"zmanjšati, saj imajo minimalno velikost. Samo onemogočite jih <menuchoice> "
"<guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Prikaži vrstico s tipkami FN</"
"guimenuitem> </menuchoice> in lahko boste spremenili velikost &krusader; po "
"vaših željah. Od različice 1.51 smo to zelo izboljšali: pri zmanjševanju "
"velikosti bodo gumbi videti kot \"F5 ..py\". Če so površine gumbov premajhne "
"za branje, bo opis orodja prikazal celotno besedilo. Najmanjša širina je 45 "
"slikovnih pik za vsak gumb."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:257
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&Samba; ISO 8859-x codepage / What to do if &krusader; does not read shared "
"folders containing special international characters?"
msgstr ""
"&Samba; Kodna stran ISO 8859-x / Kaj storiti, če &krusader; ne bere map v "
"skupni rabi, ki vsebujejo posebne mednarodne znake?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:264
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&krusader; does not handle (yet) &Samba; ISO 8859-x codepages, if you use a "
"codepage different than 8859-1 you will have to do a manual configuration. "
"Create or modify the file: <filename>~/.smb/smb.conf</filename> "
"<programlisting>[global] \n"
"          workgroup = MyWorkGroup (ex. WORKGROUP) \n"
"          client code page = MyCodePage (ex. 852)\n"
"          character set = MyCharSet (ex. ISO8859-2)\n"
"          </programlisting> You can try to configure smb.conf with "
"appropriate &systemsettings; module."
msgstr ""
"&krusader; ne obravnava (še) &Samba; Kodne strani ISO 8859-x, če uporabljate "
"kodno stran, ki ni 8859-1, boste morali izvesti ročno konfiguracijo. "
"Ustvarite ali spremenite datoteko: <filename>~/.smb/smb.conf</filename> "
"<programlisting>[global]\n"
"           delovna skupina = Moja delovna skupina (npr. DELOVNA SKUPINA)\n"
"           kodna stran odjemalca = MyCodePage (npr. 852)\n"
"           nabor znakov = MyCharSet (npr. ISO8859-2)\n"
"           </programlisting> Lahko poskusite konfigurirati smb.conf z "
"ustreznimi &systemsettings; modul."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:279
#, no-c-format
msgid "What to do if an external tool does not seem to work?"
msgstr "Kaj storiti, če se zdi, da zunanje orodje ne deluje?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:282
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&krusader; uses several programs as <link linkend=\"konfig-dependencies"
"\">external tools</link>, and sometimes they appear not to work. Open a "
"terminal and check if tool foo is installed. <screen><prompt>$</prompt> "
"<userinput><command>foo</command></userinput></screen> Check if tool foo is "
"properly configured in the <link linkend=\"konfig-dependencies"
"\">Konfigurator Dependencies page</link>. For Archiving tools: autodetect "
"the archives again with the <guibutton>Auto Configure</guibutton> button in "
"the <link linkend=\"konfig-archives\">Konfigurator archive page</link>. "
"Check the <link linkend=\"konfig-protocols\">Konfigurator Protocol page</"
"link> If it does not work, backup your <filename><envar>XDG_CONFIG_HOME</"
"envar>/krusaderrc</filename> (default is <filename>$<envar>HOME</envar>/."
"config/krusaderc</filename>) configuration file and remove it from this "
"location. Restart &krusader;, &krusader; will now start the first start "
"configuration wizard, follow these guidelines."
msgstr ""
"&krusader; uporablja več programov kot <link linkend=\"konfig-dependencies"
"\">zunanja orodja</link> in včasih se zdi, da ne delujejo. Odprite terminal "
"in preverite, ali je orodje foo nameščeno. <screen><prompt>$</prompt> "
"<userinput><command>foo</command></userinput></screen> Preverite, ali je "
"orodje foo pravilno konfigurirano v <link linkend=\"konfig-dependencies"
"\">Konfiguratorju Stran z odvisnostmi</link>. Za orodja za arhiviranje: "
"znova samodejno zaznajte arhive z gumbom <guibutton>Samodejna konfiguracija</"
"guibutton> na <link linkend=\"konfig-archives\">arhivski strani "
"konfiguratorja</link>. Preverite <link linkend=\"konfig-protocols\">stran "
"Konfigurator Protocol</link> Če ne deluje, varnostno kopirajte svoj "
"<filename><envar>XDG_CONFIG_HOME</envar>/krusaderrc</filename> (privzeto je "
"<filename> $<envar>HOME</envar>/.config/krusaderc</filename>) "
"konfiguracijsko datoteko in jo odstranite s tega mesta. Znova zaženi "
"&krusader;, &krusader; bo zdaj zagnal čarovnika za konfiguracijo prvega "
"zagona, sledite tem navodilom."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:305
#, no-c-format
msgid "How to executing jar files (and not enter the jar archive)?"
msgstr "Kako izvajati datoteke jar (in ne vstopiti v arhiv jar)?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:308
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Go to the <link linkend=\"konfig-protocols\">Konfigurator Protocol page</"
"link> and remove <guilabel>application/x-jar</guilabel> from the krarc node, "
"&krusader; should no longer enter the archive. Global file associations are "
"handled by &plasma; and not by &krusader;. To associate the jar extension:"
msgstr ""
"Pojdite na <link linkend=\"konfig-protocols\">stran Konfigurator Protocol</"
"link> in odstranite <guilabel>application/x-jar</guilabel> iz vozlišča "
"krarc, &krusader; ne sme več v arhiv. Globalne povezave datotek ureja "
"&plasma; in ne &krusader;. Če želite povezati razširitev jar:"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:314
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Open &plasma; &systemsettings;: <application>systemsettings</application>"
msgstr ""
"Odpri &plasma; &systemsettings;: <application>systemsettings</application>"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: faq.docbook:319
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Applications</guimenu> <guimenuitem>File Associations</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Aplikacije</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Povezave datotek</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:326
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enter <filename>jar</filename> as filename pattern"
msgstr "Vnesite <filename>jar</filename> kot vzorec imena datoteke"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:330
#, no-c-format
msgid "Add <filename>java</filename> as application"
msgstr "Dodajte <filename>java</filename> kot aplikacijo"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:342
#, no-c-format
msgid "Why do I have trouble with my &FTP; connection?"
msgstr "Zakaj imam težave s svojim &FTP; povezava?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:346
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This problem often occurs when you are behind a firewall or proxy. Open "
"<menuchoice> <guimenu>System Settings</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Network</"
"guimenuitem> <guimenuitem> Settings</guimenuitem> <guimenuitem>Connection "
"Preferences</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>, <guilabel>Enable Passive Mode "
"(PASV)</guilabel> has to be turned on or off, depending on its current "
"setting. Now try your &FTP; session again to see if it works. Also, make "
"sure you have no other &FTP; sessions open (using web browsers, &etc;), they "
"can cause complications. More information can be found in <ulink url="
"\"https://slacksite.com/other/ftp.html\">Active &FTP; vs. Passive &FTP;, a "
"Definitive Explanation</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Ta težava se pogosto pojavi, ko ste za požarnim zidom ali proxyjem. Odprite "
"<menuchoice> <guimenu>Sistemske nastavitve</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Omrežje</"
"guimenuitem> <guimenuitem> Nastavitve</guimenuitem> <guimenuitem>Nastavitve "
"povezave</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>, <guilabel>Omogoči pasivni način "
"( PASV)</guilabel> je treba vklopiti ali izklopiti, odvisno od trenutne "
"nastavitve. Zdaj poskusite &FTP; ponovno sejo, da vidim, ali deluje. "
"Prepričajte se tudi, da nimate drugega &FTP; odprte seje (z uporabo spletnih "
"brskalnikov &etc;), lahko povzročijo zaplete. Več informacij je na voljo v "
"<ulink url=\"https://slacksite.com/other/ftp.html\">Active &FTP; v "
"primerjavi s pasivnim &FTP;, dokončna razlaga</ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:368
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"I get <errorcode>&FTP; protocol not supported by &krusader;</errorcode> "
"error when trying to open a remote &FTP; folder, what to do?"
msgstr ""
"Dobim <errorcode>&FTP; protokola ne podpira &krusader;</errorcode> napaka "
"pri poskusu odpiranja oddaljenega &FTP; mapa, kaj narediti?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:375
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The reason for this error is that '&FTP; via &HTTP; proxy' feature is not "
"yet supported by &krusader;. This error may be caused by a misconfiguration "
"of the proxy settings in &systemsettings;. Modify the proxy settings to not "
"use &HTTP; proxy and &FTP; will work."
msgstr ""
"Razlog za to napako je, da '&FTP; prek &HTTP; funkcija proxy' &krusader; še "
"ne podpira. To napako lahko povzroči napačna konfiguracija nastavitev "
"strežnika proxy v &systemsettings;. Spremenite nastavitve proxyja, da ne "
"boste uporabljali &HTTP; proxy in &FTP; bo delovalo."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:389
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"How do not add <literal role=\"extension\">.part</literal> suffix when "
"copying files via &FTP;?"
msgstr ""
"Kako ne dodati pripone <literal role=\"extension\">.part</literal> pri "
"kopiranju datotek prek &FTP;?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:392
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When uploading files a <literal role=\"extension\">.part</literal> suffix is "
"added to the filename, once the upload is complete the filename is renamed "
"automagically to remove the <literal role=\"extension\">.part</literal> "
"suffix. This works great but sometimes some &FTP; servers do not allow a "
"rename operation. You can solve this by unchecking the checkbox "
"<guilabel>Mark partially uploaded files</guilabel> in &plasma; "
"&systemsettings;. The check box is located at <menuchoice> <guimenu>Network</"
"guimenu> <guimenuitem>Settings</guimenuitem> <guimenuitem>Connection "
"Preferences</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>."
msgstr ""
"Pri nalaganju datotek se imenu datoteke doda pripona <literal role="
"\"extension\">.part</literal>, ko je nalaganje končano, se ime datoteke "
"samodejno preimenuje, da se odstrani <literal role=\"extension\">.part</"
"literal> pripona. To deluje odlično, vendar včasih nekaj &FTP; strežniki ne "
"dovoljujejo operacije preimenovanja. To lahko rešite tako, da počistite "
"potrditveno polje <guilabel>Označi delno naložene datoteke</guilabel> v "
"&plasma; &systemsettings;. Potrditveno polje je v <menuchoice> "
"<guimenu>Omrežje</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Nastavitve</guimenuitem> "
"<guimenuitem>Možnosti povezave</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:410
#, no-c-format
msgid "How can I close a remote connection (&eg; a &FTP; connection)?"
msgstr "Kako lahko zaprem oddaljeno povezavo (&eg; &FTP; povezavo)?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:414
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is explained in the <link linkend=\"remote-connections\">remote "
"connections chapter</link>."
msgstr ""
"Razloženo je v <link linkend=\"remote-connections\">poglavju o oddaljenih "
"povezavah</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:423
#, no-c-format
msgid "I am experiencing problems with the media:/ protocol, why?"
msgstr "Imam težave s protokolom media:/, zakaj?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:427
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The media:/ protocol was removed since &kde; 4. Please use mtp:/ protocol "
"instead."
msgstr ""
"Protokol media:/ je bil odstranjen, ker &kde; 4. Namesto tega uporabite "
"protokol mtp:/."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:435
#, no-c-format
msgid "How can I disable the default sounds, &eg; when I do a delete action?"
msgstr ""
"Kako lahko onemogočim privzete zvoke, &eg; ko izvedem dejanje brisanja?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:439
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Those are the default &plasma; System sounds, and not related to &krusader;. "
"If you want to disable them globally open your &plasma; &systemsettings; "
"( <application>systemsettings</application>): <menuchoice> "
"<guimenu>Personalization</guimenu> <guisubmenu>Notifications</guisubmenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Manage Notifications</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>, "
"<guilabel>Event Source: \"Plasma Workspace\" </guilabel> and uncheck sound "
"items you do not like."
msgstr ""
"To so privzeti &plasma; Sistemski zvoki, ki niso povezani z &krusader;. Če "
"jih želite globalno onemogočiti, odprite svoj &plasma; &systemsettings; "
"( <application>systemsettings</application>): <menuchoice> "
"<guimenu>Prilagajanje</guimenu> <guisubmenu>Obvestila</guisubmenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Upravljanje obvestil</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>, <guilabel>Vir "
"dogodka: \"Plasma Workspace\" </guilabel> in počistite zvočne elemente, ki "
"vam niso všeč."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:458
#, no-c-format
msgid "Where the remote connection manager?"
msgstr "Kje je upravitelj oddaljenih povezav?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:461
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use our Bookmark Manager. Use a <link linkend=\"remote-connections\">remote "
"&URL;</link> and bookmark it."
msgstr ""
"Uporabite našega upravitelja zaznamkov. Uporabite <link linkend=\"remote-"
"connections\">oddaljeni &URL;</link> in ga dodajte med zaznamke."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:470
#, no-c-format
msgid "Why does not &MIME; type magic sometimes work inside archives?"
msgstr "Zakaj &MIME; type magic včasih deluje znotraj arhivov?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:474
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you enter an archive and press <keycap>F3</keycap> to view a file that "
"has no known extension, &eg; <filename>README, INSTALL</filename> &etc; And "
"if the viewer opens in hex-mode instead of the usual mode, than you need to "
"configure: <menuchoice> <guimenu>&kde; System Settings</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>File Associations</guimenuitem> <guimenuitem>Application</"
"guimenuitem> <guimenuitem>octet-stream</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>, "
"<guilabel>binary viewer</guilabel> needs to be removed."
msgstr ""
"Ko vstopite v arhiv in pritisnete <keycap>F3</keycap>, da si ogledate "
"datoteko, ki nima znane končnice, &eg; <filename>PREBERI ME, NAMESTI</"
"filename> &etc; In če se pregledovalnik odpre v hex-načinu namesto v "
"običajnem načinu, potem morate konfigurirati: <menuchoice> <guimenu>&kde; "
"Sistemske nastavitve</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Povezave datotek</guimenuitem> "
"<guimenuitem>Aplikacija</guimenuitem> <guimenuitem>octet-stream</"
"guimenuitem> </menuchoice>, <guilabel>binarni pregledovalnik</guilabel> mora "
"biti odstranili."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:495
#, no-c-format
msgid "Where is Konfigurator, do i need to install the &plasma; to use it?"
msgstr "Kje je Konfigurator, ali moram namestiti &plasma; ga uporabiti?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:498
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"konfigurator\">Konfigurator</link> is &krusader;s "
"configuration module, if you have installed &krusader; then you have also "
"Konfigurator. For some reason some people think it is an other &plasma; "
"application, but it is not, so you do not need to install the full fledged "
"&plasma; to use Konfigurator. When running &krusader;, use <menuchoice> "
"<guimenu>Settings</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Configure &krusader;...</"
"guimenuitem> </menuchoice>, and it will start <link linkend=\"konfigurator"
"\">Konfigurator</link>. Please read the manual, &krusader; has many many "
"configuration options, a lot of things can be customized to your needs with "
"<link linkend=\"konfigurator\">Konfigurator</link>."
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"konfigurator\">Konfigurator</link> je konfiguracijski modul "
"&krusader;, če ste namestili &krusader; potem imate tudi Konfigurator. Iz "
"nekega razloga nekateri mislijo, da gre za drugo &plasma; vendar ni, zato "
"vam ni treba namestiti popolne &plasma; za uporabo Konfiguratorja. Ko "
"izvajate &krusader;, uporabite <menuchoice> <guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Konfiguriraj &krusader;...</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> in "
"zagnal se bo <link linkend=\"konfigurator\">Konfigurator</link>. Preberite "
"priročnik, &krusader; ima veliko možnosti konfiguracije, veliko stvari lahko "
"prilagodite svojim potrebam s <link linkend=\"konfigurator"
"\">Konfiguratorjem</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:518
#, no-c-format
msgid "How can I set the look &amp; feel of 2 different users to be the same?"
msgstr ""
"Kako lahko nastavim videz &amp; občutek, da sta 2 različna uporabnika enaka?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:522
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Presuming that the current setup is the good configuration, you can copy the "
"configuration to the other user. <screen><prompt>#</prompt> "
"<userinput><command>cp ~/.config/krusaderrc /home/foo_user/.config</"
"command></userinput></screen> And when the other user is Root use:"
msgstr ""
"Ob predpostavki, da je trenutna nastavitev dobra konfiguracija, lahko "
"konfiguracijo kopirate drugemu uporabniku. <screen><prompt>#</prompt> "
"<userinput><command>cp ~/.config/krusaderrc /home/foo_user/.config</"
"command></userinput></screen> In ko je drugi uporabnik Root uporaba:"

#. Tag: screen
#: faq.docbook:527
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<prompt>#</prompt> <userinput><command>cp ~/.config/krusaderrc /root/."
"config</command></userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<prompt>#</prompt> <userinput><command>cp ~/.config/krusaderrc /root/."
"config</command></userinput>"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:536
#, no-c-format
msgid "How to customize the embedded terminal of &krusader;?"
msgstr "Kako prilagoditi vdelan terminal &krusader;?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:539
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In order to change properties of the embedded terminal emulator of "
"&krusader;: you can right-click on it and choose an option, and if you don't "
"find there what you are looking for, you can use the <menuchoice> "
"<guimenu>Settings</guimenu> </menuchoice> menu of &konsole; (because "
"&krusader; uses a &konsole; KPart for its embedded terminal). In that menu, "
"other items are seen (like <menuchoice> <guimenuitem>\"Manage Profiles...\"</"
"guimenuitem> </menuchoice>)."
msgstr ""
"Če želite spremeniti lastnosti vdelanega terminalskega emulatorja "
"&krusader;: lahko ga kliknete z desno tipko miške in izberete možnost, in če "
"tam ne najdete tistega, kar iščete, lahko uporabite <menuchoice> <guimenu> "
"Nastavitve</guimenu> </menuchoice> meni &konsole; (ker &krusader; uporablja "
"&konsole; KPart za svoj vdelani terminal). V tem meniju so prikazani drugi "
"elementi (na primer <menuchoice> <guimenuitem>»Upravljanje profilov ...«</"
"guimenuitem> </menuchoice>)."

#. Tag: title
#: faq.docbook:563
#, no-c-format
msgid "General &FAQ;"
msgstr "Splošno &FAQ;"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:567
#, no-c-format
msgid "How can I report a wish, a suggestion, or a comment?"
msgstr "Kako lahko prijavim željo, predlog ali komentar?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:571
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An open source project's greatest strength is derived from getting user "
"feedback. That is why we love to hear what you have to say. Your "
"<quote>gripes</quote> are our instructions. After about 6 months, "
"programmers can no longer see their own mistakes. It is natural. We want the "
"ideas, qritiques, and feedback because we all want to make &krusader; the "
"best and most useful file manager available anywhere."
msgstr ""
"Največja moč odprtokodnega projekta izhaja iz pridobivanja povratnih "
"informacij uporabnikov. Zato radi slišimo, kaj imate povedati. Vaši "
"<quote>prijemi</quote> so naša navodila. Po približno 6 mesecih programerji "
"ne vidijo več lastnih napak. To je naravno. Želimo ideje, kritike in "
"povratne informacije, ker vsi želimo narediti &krusader; najboljši in "
"najbolj uporaben upravitelj datotek, ki je na voljo povsod."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:579
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The most convenient way to contact us is to use the krusader-users <ulink "
"url=\"https://krusader.org/get-involved/mailing-lists/index.html\">mailing "
"list</ulink>. For information on what remains to be done look at the <ulink "
"url=\"https://groups.google.com/group/krusader-devel\">&krusader;-devel "
"mailing list</ulink>. We review and discuss every submission."
msgstr ""
"Najprimernejši način za stik z nami je uporaba <ulink url=\"https://krusader."
"org/get-involved/mailing-lists/index.html\">poštnega seznama</ulink> "
"krusader-users. Za informacije o tem, kaj je še treba narediti, si oglejte "
"<ulink url=\"https://groups.google.com/group/krusader-devel\">&krusader;-"
"devel poštni seznam</ulink>. Vsako prijavo pregledamo in se o njej "
"pogovorimo."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:590
#, no-c-format
msgid "How can I send a patch?"
msgstr "Kako lahko pošljem popravek?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:593
#, no-c-format
msgid "It is not easy to write patch guidelines, but here are some."
msgstr "Smernic za popravke ni enostavno napisati, a tukaj jih je nekaj."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:597
#, no-c-format
msgid "Patches, new code or new features are always welcome!"
msgstr "Popravki, nova koda ali nove funkcije so vedno dobrodošle!"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:601
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Focus only on one problem at a time, so the developers can easily understand "
"you, and commit your patch it works."
msgstr ""
"Osredotočite se samo na eno težavo naenkrat, da vas bodo razvijalci zlahka "
"razumeli in izdali vaš popravek, da deluje."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:606
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Preferably, you can start a discussion with the developers on the krusader-"
"devel <ulink url=\"https://krusader.org/get-involved/mailing-lists/index.html"
"\">mailing lists</ulink> or on the <ulink url=\"https://invent.kde.org/"
"utilities/krusader/-/merge_requests\">&krusader; GitLab page</ulink>. "
"Unfortunately, we cannot apply a patch if the patch is in conflict with the "
"<quote>general design</quote> of the &krusader; code (read for more "
"instructions in this FAQ). Please send only one change request per mail, so "
"that the discussion is easier to follow. The modifications should be "
"committed step by step, checking each line."
msgstr ""
"Po možnosti lahko začnete razpravo z razvijalci na krusader-devel <ulink url="
"\"https://krusader.org/get-involved/mailing-lists/index.html\">poštnih "
"seznamih</ulink> ali na <ulink url=\"https://invent.kde.org/utilities/"
"krusader/-/merge_requests\">&krusader; Stran GitLab</ulink>. Na žalost ne "
"moremo uporabiti popravka, če je popravek v nasprotju s <quote>splošnim "
"dizajnom</quote> datoteke &krusader; kodo (za več navodil preberite ta "
"pogosta vprašanja). Prosimo, pošljite samo eno zahtevo za spremembo na e-"
"pošto, da boste razpravi lažje sledili. Spremembe je treba izvajati korak za "
"korakom in preveriti vsako vrstico."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:620
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Submit your patch files on the <ulink url=\"https://invent.kde.org/utilities/"
"krusader/-/merge_requests\">GitLab</ulink>, so that all patch proposals stay "
"organised and do not get lost, tar.gz archives or diffs are usually ok. Do "
"not copy changes into a mail. Most mailers will change the white spaces, so "
"that the diff will not apply or the code snipped does not diff. In the past, "
"patch mails went lost or disorganized in many many mails, so please use the "
"<ulink url=\"https://community.kde.org/Infrastructure/GitLab\">GitLab</"
"ulink>, thanks!"
msgstr ""
"Pošljite svoje datoteke popravkov v <ulink url=\"https://invent.kde.org/"
"utilities/krusader/-/merge_requests\">GitLab</ulink>, da bodo vsi predlogi "
"popravkov ostali organizirani in se ne bodo izgubili, tar .gz arhivi ali "
"razlike so običajno v redu. Ne kopirajte sprememb v pošto. Večina "
"pošiljateljev bo spremenila bele prostore, tako da diff ne bo veljal ali pa "
"izrezana koda ne bo diff. V preteklosti so se popravki izgubili ali bili "
"neorganizirani v številnih pismih, zato uporabite <ulink url=\"https://"
"community.kde.org/Infrastructure/GitLab\">GitLab</ulink>, hvala!"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:630
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use portable solutions, &krusader; should run on: <itemizedlist> <listitem> "
"<para>All POSIX (&Linux;/BSD/&UNIX;-like OSes), &Solaris;.</para> </"
"listitem> <listitem> <para>All BSD Platforms (<trademark class=\"copyright"
"\">FreeBSD</trademark>/<trademark class=\"registered\">NetBSD</trademark>/"
"<trademark class=\"registered\">OpenBSD</trademark>/&MacOS;).</para> </"
"listitem> <listitem> <para>&kde; 3.3- &kde; 3.5 and even on GNOME with "
"kdelibs (for &krusader;-2.x) .</para> </listitem> <listitem> <para>GCC 2.95 "
"- GCC 5.4</para> </listitem> </itemizedlist>Architecture changes are made by "
"the team only."
msgstr ""
"Uporabite prenosne rešitve, &krusader; bi moral delovati na: <itemizedlist> "
"<listitem> <para>Vse POSIX (&Linux;/BSD/&UNIX; podobni operacijski sistemi), "
"&Solaris;.</para> </listitem> <listitem> <para>Vse platforme BSD (<trademark "
"class=\"copyright\">FreeBSD</trademark>/<trademark class=\"registered"
"\">NetBSD</trademark>/<trademark class=\"registered\">OpenBSD</trademark>/"
"&MacOS;).</para> </listitem> <listitem> <para>&kde; 3.3- &kde; 3.5 in celo v "
"GNOME s kdelibs (za &krusader;-2.x) .</para> </listitem> <listitem> "
"<para>GCC 2.95 - GCC 5.4</para> </listitem> </itemizedlist>Spremembe "
"arhitekture jih izdeluje samo ekipa."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:654
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A final note: always keep in mind a patch might be rejected. Either it has "
"side effects, which we could not fix or it contradicts with the idea behind "
"the patched module. In this sense, a software project differs from, let's "
"say a wiki: a software project has to have someone to make all the final "
"decisions. Otherwise the software will not work. Furthermore: keep in mind "
"that the examination of patches might take time, as we all have private "
"lives."
msgstr ""
"Zadnja opomba: vedno upoštevajte, da bo popravek lahko zavrnjen. Ali ima "
"stranske učinke, ki jih nismo mogli odpraviti, ali pa je v nasprotju z idejo "
"za popravljenim modulom. V tem smislu se programski projekt razlikuje od, "
"recimo, wikija: programski projekt mora imeti nekoga, ki sprejema vse končne "
"odločitve. V nasprotnem primeru programska oprema ne bo delovala. Poleg "
"tega: ne pozabite, da lahko pregled obližev traja nekaj časa, saj imamo vsi "
"zasebno življenje."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:671
#, no-c-format
msgid "How can I report a bug?"
msgstr "Kako lahko prijavim napako?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:674
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bugs?!?!? Well, ok.... We have an online Bug Tracking System."
msgstr "Napake?!?!? No, v redu.... Imamo spletni sistem za sledenje napakam."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:676
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using the online bug-tracker helps us have a clear and orderly way to know "
"how many bugs are open, bug priority and follow-ups. It saves us from "
"browsing through the entire &krusader; forum, searching for yesterdays bug. "
"Please use this system."
msgstr ""
"Uporaba spletnega sledilnika hroščev nam pomaga imeti jasen in urejen način, "
"da vemo, koliko hroščev je odprtih, prioriteto hroščev in nadaljnje ukrepe. "
"Prihrani nam brskanje po celotnem &krusader; forum, iščem včerajšnjo napako. "
"Prosimo, uporabite ta sistem."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:681
#, no-c-format
msgid "Before reporting a bug, please read the following:"
msgstr "Preden prijavite napako, preberite naslednje:"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:684
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Check</emphasis> if the bug is already posted in the "
"<ulink url=\"https://bugs.kde.org\">online bug list</ulink> of the Bug "
"Tracking System."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Preverite</emphasis>, če je napaka že objavljena na "
"<ulink url=\"https://bugs.kde.org\">spletnem seznamu napak</ulink> sistema "
"za sledenje napakam."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:690
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you cannot find this bug mentioned, please <emphasis role=\"bold"
"\">submit</emphasis> it into the bug tracker by clicking the "
"<guibutton>Submit New</guibutton> button in the bug-tracker window. Please "
"submit the following issues: the &krusader; version used, the &Linux; "
"distribution + version used, processor type, and as good a description of "
"the problem as you can manage."
msgstr ""
"Če ne najdete omenjene te napake, jo <emphasis role=\"bold\">predložite</"
"emphasis> v sledilnik hroščev s klikom na gumb <guibutton>Pošlji novo</"
"guibutton> v oknu sledilnika hroščev. Predložite naslednje težave: "
"&krusader; uporabljena različica &Linux; distribucija + uporabljena "
"različica, vrsta procesorja in čim boljši opis težave."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:703
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If possible, try to do the same operation with &konqueror; or another &kde; "
"application. If you encounter the same problem then it is possibly a KIO "
"Slaves or &kf5-full; bug, and not a &krusader; bug. &krusader; uses the &kde-"
"frameworks; libraries and the KIO Slave for many operations. In some cases "
"you can encounter problems if your distribution is incorrectly configured, "
"please test it first as explained above."
msgstr ""
"Če je možno, poskusite narediti isto operacijo s &konqueror; ali drug &kde; "
"aplikacija. Če naletite na isto težavo, potem gre verjetno za KIO Slaves ali "
"&kf5-full; napaka in ne &krusader; napaka. &krusader; uporablja &kde-"
"frameworks; knjižnice in KIO Slave za številne operacije. V nekaterih "
"primerih lahko naletite na težave, če je vaša distribucija nepravilno "
"konfigurirana, najprej jo preizkusite, kot je razloženo zgoraj."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:724
#, no-c-format
msgid "How can i send good debug or crash reports?"
msgstr "Kako lahko pošljem dobra poročila o odpravljanju napak ali zrušitvah?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:727
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Usually binary packages that are been used by your distribution do not "
"contain debug information. Since we usually only develop and fix &krusader;-"
"git, compile &krusader;-git in debugmode and install it, than check if the "
"bug still exist. <screen><prompt>$</prompt> <userinput><command>cmake</"
"command> <option>-DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=debugfull</option></userinput></screen> "
"Install <ulink url=\"https://valgrind.org\">valgrind</ulink>, a suite of "
"tools for debugging and profiling &Linux; programs. Run Valgrind/&krusader; "
"<screen><prompt>$</prompt> <userinput><command>valgrind</command> <option>--"
"tool=memcheck</option> <replaceable>{foo_path}/krusader</replaceable></"
"userinput></screen> The valgrind tool will write to stdout, what really "
"happens. If you could send these information before the crash, it is almost "
"sure, that we may fix or tell you what to do."
msgstr ""
"Običajno binarni paketi, ki jih uporablja vaša distribucija, ne vsebujejo "
"informacij o odpravljanju napak. Ker običajno samo razvijamo in popravljamo "
"&krusader;-git, prevedite &krusader;-git v načinu za odpravljanje napak in "
"ga namestite, nato pa preverite, ali napaka še obstaja. <screen><prompt>$</"
"prompt> <userinput><command>cmake</command> <option>-"
"DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=debugfull</option></userinput></screen> Namestite <ulink "
"url=\"https:/ /valgrind.org\">valgrind</ulink>, nabor orodij za odpravljanje "
"napak in profiliranje &Linux; programi. Zaženite Valgrind/&krusader; "
"<screen><prompt>$</prompt> <userinput><command>valgrind</command> <option>--"
"tool=memcheck</option> <replaceable>{foo_path}/krusader</replaceable></"
"userinput> </screen> Orodje valgrind bo zapisalo v stdout, kaj se v resnici "
"zgodi. Če bi te informacije lahko poslali pred zrušitvijo, je skoraj gotovo, "
"da bomo morda popravili ali vam povedali, kaj morate storiti."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:745
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"What to do if the KDEcrashhandler sends no useful backtrace information?"
msgstr ""
"Kaj storiti, če KDEcrashhandler ne pošlje nobenih uporabnih informacij o "
"povratnem sledenju?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:748
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Usually binary packages that are been used by your distribution do not "
"contain debug information. Since we usually only develop and fix &krusader;-"
"git, compile &krusader;-git in debugmode and install it, than check if the "
"bug still exist. <screen><prompt>$</prompt> <userinput><command>cmake</"
"command> <option>-DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=debugfull</option></userinput></screen> "
"If the KDEKrashhandler still does not provide useful backtrace information, "
"than sometimes a coredump will give better information. Run Krusader, with "
"disabled crashhandler. <screen><prompt>$</prompt> "
"<userinput><command>krusader</command> <option>--nocrashhandler</option></"
"userinput></screen> On a crash you will get a <filename>.core</filename> "
"file, usually in your home folder. Run <ulink url=\"https://sourceware.org/"
"gdb/\">gdb</ulink>, the GNU Project Debugger <screen><prompt>$</prompt> "
"<userinput><command>gdb</command> <option>-c</option> <replaceable>corefile "
"krusader</replaceable></userinput></screen> Now type <command>bt</command> "
"to get the backtrace and type <command>q</command> to quit gdb. Often the "
"best debug results will be given when using the valgrind tool."
msgstr ""
"Običajno binarni paketi, ki jih uporablja vaša distribucija, ne vsebujejo "
"informacij o odpravljanju napak. Ker običajno samo razvijamo in popravljamo "
"&krusader;-git, prevedite &krusader;-git v načinu za odpravljanje napak in "
"ga namestite, nato pa preverite, ali napaka še obstaja. <screen><prompt>$</"
"prompt> <userinput><command>cmake</command> <option>-"
"DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=debugfull</option></userinput></screen> Če KDEKrashhandler "
"še vedno ne nudi uporabne povratne sledi informacije, kot včasih bo coredump "
"dal boljše informacije. Zaženite Krusader z onemogočenim obdelovalcem "
"zrušitev. <screen><prompt>$</prompt> <userinput><command>krusader</command> "
"<option>--nocrashhandler</option></userinput></screen> Ob zrušitvi boste "
"prejeli <filename> .core</filename>, običajno v domači mapi. Zaženite <ulink "
"url=\"https://sourceware.org/gdb/\">gdb</ulink>, GNU Project Debugger "
"<screen><prompt>$</prompt> <userinput><command>gdb</command> <option>-c</"
"option> <replaceable>corefile krusader</replaceable></userinput></screen> "
"Zdaj vnesite <command>bt</command>, da dobite povratno sled, in vnesite "
"<command>q</command> zapreti gdb. Pogosto so najboljši rezultati "
"odpravljanja napak pri uporabi orodja valgrind."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:772
#, no-c-format
msgid "Does &krusader; have a mailing list?"
msgstr "Ali &krusader; imate poštni seznam?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:776
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Yes, currently we have several <ulink url=\"https://krusader.org/get-"
"involved/mailing-lists/index.html\">mailing lists</ulink>. No spam, no "
"bother, just &krusader;. Feel free to subscribe and unsubscribe."
msgstr ""
"Da, trenutno imamo več <ulink url=\"https://krusader.org/get-involved/"
"mailing-lists/index.html\">poštnih seznamov</ulink>. Brez vsiljene pošte, "
"brez skrbi, samo &krusader;. Lahko se naročite in odjavite."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:780
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Tip. our mailing lists can be browsed online or read with a newsreader, so "
"that you do not even need to subscribe to follow the action on the mailing "
"lists."
msgstr ""
"Namig. po naših poštnih seznamih lahko brskate na spletu ali jih berete z "
"bralnikom novic, tako da se vam za spremljanje dogajanja na poštnih seznamih "
"sploh ni treba naročiti."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:785
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://groups.google.com/group/krusader-devel\">&krusader;-"
"devel</ulink> is the developer mailing list (read-only). If you want to "
"follow the development of &krusader; on the cutting edge, this is the list "
"to follow."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"https://groups.google.com/group/krusader-devel\">&krusader;-"
"devel</ulink> je poštni seznam razvijalcev (samo za branje). Če želite "
"slediti razvoju &krusader; na vrhuncu, to je seznam, ki mu sledi."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:791
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://groups.google.com/group/krusader-users\">&krusader;-"
"users</ulink> is the &krusader; users mailing list. Here you can ask for "
"help and talk with the &krusader; users and developers."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"https://groups.google.com/group/krusader-users\">&krusader;-"
"users</ulink> je &krusader; poštni seznam uporabnikov. Tukaj lahko zaprosite "
"za pomoč in se pogovorite z &krusader; uporabniki in razvijalci."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:797
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"http://groups.google.com/group/krusader-news\">&krusader;-news</"
"ulink> is a very low volume list, used for announcements of new versions or "
"critical bugfixes."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"http://groups.google.com/group/krusader-news\">&krusader;-news</"
"ulink> je zelo majhen seznam, ki se uporablja za objave novih različic ali "
"kritičnih popravkov napak."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:808
#, no-c-format
msgid "Does &krusader; provide news feeds?"
msgstr "Ali &krusader; zagotoviti vire novic?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:812
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Yes, we do. Several news feeds in various formats are available. <ulink url="
"\"https://groups.google.com/group/krusader-devel/feeds\">krusader-devel "
"feed</ulink>, <ulink url=\"https://groups.google.com/group/krusader-users/"
"feeds\">krusader-users feed</ulink> and <ulink url=\"https://groups.google."
"com/group/krusader-news/feeds\">krusader-news feed</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Da, imamo. Na voljo je več virov novic v različnih formatih. <ulink url="
"\"https://groups.google.com/group/krusader-devel/feeds\">vir krusader-devel</"
"ulink>, <ulink url=\"https://groups.google.com/group/krusader-users/feeds"
"\">krusader-users vir</ulink> in <ulink url=\"https://groups.google.com/"
"group/krusader-news/feeds\">krusader-news vir</ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:822
#, no-c-format
msgid "How does the &krusader; forum work?"
msgstr "Kako deluje &krusader; delo na forumu?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:826
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the spirit of freedom of speech, everything that is &krusader; related "
"can be discussed in our forum. It does not matter if you are a newcomer or "
"an advanced user, everyone is welcome. An open source project's greatest "
"strength is derived from getting user feedback. That is why we love to hear "
"what you have to say. With your feedback we can make &krusader; better and "
"better; otherwise, we are not aware of issues and ideas you may have. But "
"please remember the following, so that we can maintain some order in the "
"chaos."
msgstr ""
"V duhu svobode govora je vse, kar je &krusader; o tem lahko razpravljate na "
"našem forumu. Ni važno, ali ste novinec ali napreden uporabnik, vsi so "
"dobrodošli. Največja moč odprtokodnega projekta izhaja iz pridobivanja "
"povratnih informacij uporabnikov. Zato radi slišimo, kaj imate povedati. Z "
"vašimi povratnimi informacijami lahko naredimo &krusader; boljši in boljši; "
"sicer nismo seznanjeni s težavami in idejami, ki jih morda imate. Zapomnite "
"pa si naslednje, da bomo lahko ohranili nekaj reda v kaosu."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:837
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the <link linkend=\"index\">Documentation</link>, <link linkend=\"faq"
"\">FAQ</link> and <ulink url=\"https://groups.google.com/group/krusader-devel"
"\">&krusader;-devel</ulink> (please use the search function ) cannot help "
"you, do not hesitate to post on our forum. The &krusader; Krew or the "
"&krusader; community is always available to help you."
msgstr ""
"Če <link linkend=\"index\">Dokumentacija</link>, <link linkend=\"faq"
"\">pogosta vprašanja</link> in <ulink url=\"https://groups.google.com/group/"
"krusader-devel\">&krusader;-devel</ulink> (prosimo, uporabite funkcijo "
"iskanja ) vam ne more pomagati, ne oklevajte z objavo na našem forumu. "
"&krusader; Krew ali &krusader; skupnost vam je vedno na voljo, da vam pomaga."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:845
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Please use the search function of the <ulink url=\"https://forum.kde.org/"
"viewforum.php?f=225\">&kde; Forum</ulink>, your issue may have been "
"previously discussed (this allows us to minimize the double/triple/... "
"postings). If your issue has already been discussed in the past there is a "
"great chance that you will have an instant solution to your problem. If the "
"issue is currently being discussed, you can join in the discussion. Some "
"questions are asked over and over again, that is why we have created this "
"<link linkend=\"faq\">FAQ</link>. This allows us to spend more time "
"developing &krusader;."
msgstr ""
"Uporabite iskalno funkcijo <ulink url=\"https://forum.kde.org/viewforum.php?"
"f=225\">&kde; Forum</ulink>, o vaši težavi so morda že razpravljali (to nam "
"omogoča, da zmanjšamo število dvojnih/trojnih/... objav). Če so o vaši "
"težavi v preteklosti že razpravljali, obstaja velika verjetnost, da boste "
"imeli takojšnjo rešitev za svojo težavo. Če se o vprašanju trenutno "
"razpravlja, se lahko pridružite razpravi. Nekatera vprašanja se postavljajo "
"znova in znova, zato smo ustvarili ta <link linkend=\"faq\">pogosta "
"vprašanja</link>. To nam omogoča, da porabimo več časa za razvoj &krusader;."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:914
#, no-c-format
msgid "How can I translate &krusader; into my native language?"
msgstr "Kako lahko prevedem &krusader; v moj materni jezik?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:918
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are interested in translating the &krusader; &GUI; or documentation, "
"please contact the <ulink url=\"https://l10n.kde.org/teams-list.php\">KDE "
"translation team</ulink> of your language."
msgstr ""
"Če vas zanima prevod &krusader; &GUI; ali dokumentacijo, se obrnite na "
"<ulink url=\"https://l10n.kde.org/teams-list.php\">prevajalsko ekipo KDE</"
"ulink> vašega jezika."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:926
#, no-c-format
msgid "How can I support &krusader;?"
msgstr "Kako lahko podprem &krusader;?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:929
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can <link linkend=\"help_krusader\"> support</link> &krusader; in many "
"different ways. Please send us <link linkend=\"faqg_wish\">feedback</link>, "
"<link linkend=\"faqg_bug_report\">bug reports</link>, patches, <link linkend="
"\"help_krusader\">donations</link>, translations, ..."
msgstr ""
"Lahko <link linkend=\"help_krusader\"> podprete</link> &krusader; na veliko "
"različnih načinov. Pošljite nam <link linkend=\"faqg_wish\">povratne "
"informacije</link>, <link linkend=\"faqg_bug_report\">poročila o napakah</"
"link>, popravke, <link linkend=\"help_krusader\">donacije</link>, "
"prevode, ..."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:943
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Why is &konqueror; in <quote>Midnight Commander style</quote> not an <link "
"linkend=\"gloss-ofm\">OFM</link>?"
msgstr ""
"Zakaj je &konqueror; v <quote>slogu Midnight Commander</quote> ni <link "
"linkend=\"gloss-ofm\">OFM</link>?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:948
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The two panels and a commandline are available, all the other stuff like "
"<link linkend=\"features\">OFM features</link> and the <link linkend=\"gloss-"
"ofm\">OFM</link> interaction with the user is missing from this profile."
msgstr ""
"Na voljo sta dve plošči in ukazna vrstica, vse druge stvari, kot so <link "
"linkend=\"features\">funkcije OFM</link> in <link linkend=\"gloss-ofm\">OFM</"
"link> interakcija z uporabnikom manjka v tem profilu."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:959
#, no-c-format
msgid "Why should I use an <link linkend=\"gloss-ofm\">OFM</link>?"
msgstr "Zakaj naj uporabljam <link linkend=\"gloss-ofm\">OFM</link>?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:963
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An <ulink url=\"https://www.softpanorama.org/OFM/index.shtml\">Orthodox File "
"Manager (OFM)</ulink> is much faster than a one panel filemanager and faster "
"than the command line. If you would like to know <ulink url=\"https://www."
"softpedia.com/reviews/linux/Krusader-18193.shtml\"> how &krusader; feels</"
"ulink>, there is only one way to discover: install it on your computer and "
"use it for a while. If you prefer to waste time and lose productivity, "
"continue to use one panel filemanagers which are based on &Windows; "
"Explorer. Matej Urban&ccaron;i&ccaron; has written a <ulink url=\"https://"
"murban.blogspot.com/2006/01/krusader-and-konqueror-twin-versus-one.html\"> "
"blog</ulink> on why <link linkend=\"gloss-ofm\">OFM</link> is better than a "
"one panel filemanager."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"https://www.softpanorama.org/OFM/index.shtml\">Ortodox File "
"Manager (OFM)</ulink> je veliko hitrejši od enodelnega upravitelja datotek "
"in hitrejši od ukazne vrstice. Če bi radi izvedeli <ulink url=\"https://www."
"softpedia.com/reviews/linux/Krusader-18193.shtml\"> kako &krusader; čuti</"
"ulink>, obstaja samo en način za odkrivanje: namestite ga na svoj računalnik "
"in ga nekaj časa uporabljajte. Če raje izgubljate čas in izgubljate "
"produktivnost, še naprej uporabljajte upravljalnike datotek z eno ploščo, ki "
"temeljijo na &Windows; Raziskovalec. Matej Urban&ccaron;i&ccaron; je napisal "
"<ulink url=\"https://murban.blogspot.com/2006/01/krusader-and-konqueror-twin-"
"versus-one.html\"> blog</ulink> o tem, zakaj <link linkend=\"gloss-ofm"
"\">OFM</link> je boljši kot enodelni upravitelj datotek."
